drwxrwxr-x 2 raakin raakin 4096 Aug 24 06:19 newc
drwxr-xr-x 2 raakin raakin 4096 Aug 18 10:27 Pictures
drwxr-xr-x 2 raakin raakin 4096 Aug 17 14:51 Public
drwx------ 8 raakin raakin 4096 Aug 18 10:33 snap
drwxr-xr-x 2 raakin raakin 4096 Aug 17 14:51 Templates
drwxr-xr-x 2 raakin raakin 4096 Aug 17 14:51 Videos
remark:
s -l lists all files and directories in the current directory in a detailed, long format.
--------------------------------------------------------------------
11)ls -m:
description:
 -m     fill width with a comma separated list of entries
output:
raakin@ubuntu-25:~$ ls -m
Desktop, Documents, Downloads, linx, Music, newc, Pictures, Public, snap, Templates, Videos
remark:
ls -m displays the contents of a directory in a single line, with each entry separated by a comma.
---------------------------------------------------------------------
12)ls -n:
description:
-n, --numeric-uid-gid
              like -l, but list numeric user and group IDs
output:
raakin@ubuntu-25:~$ ls -n
total 44
drwxr-xr-x 2 1000 1000 4096 Aug 17 14:51 Desktop
drwxr-xr-x 2 1000 1000 4096 Aug 17 14:51 Documents
drwxr-xr-x 2 1000 1000 4096 Aug 19 10:56 Downloads
drwxrwxr-x 2 1000 1000 4096 Aug 18 10:18 linx
drwxr-xr-x 2 1000 1000 4096 Aug 17 14:51 Music
drwxrwxr-x 2 1000 1000 4096 Aug 24 06:19 newc
drwxr-xr-x 2 1000 1000 4096 Aug 18 10:27 Pictures
drwxr-xr-x 2 1000 1000 4096 Aug 17 14:51 Public
drwx------ 8 1000 1000 4096 Aug 18 10:33 snap
drwxr-xr-x 2 1000 1000 4096 Aug 17 14:51 Templates
drwxr-xr-x 2 1000 1000 4096 Aug 17 14:51 Videos
remark:
ls -n displays a long list of directory contents, but it uses the user and group ID numbers instead of their names.
